    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="417" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <head>No. 416.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 3, 1883</date>.
                            (Received September 20.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 683.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I transmit herewith a copy of Consul Viosca’s
                        dispatch to me, No. 13, 17th August last, which informs me that the circuit
                        court at Culiacan has fully confirmed the sentence imposed by the district
                        court at La Paz upon Captain Caleb, of the American schooner Adriana, and
                        that that schooner was to have been sold in a few days (after the date of
                        his dispatch).</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>P. H. MORGAN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 683.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Viosca</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Morgan</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Consulate</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">La Paz,
                                        Mexico</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-08-17">
                                <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 17,
                                1883</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: It has been reported from Mazatlan that in
                            the appeal of the Adriana case pending before the United Mexican States
                            circuit court at Culiacan, decision has been rendered by the said court
                            fully confirming the sentence of the district court here.</p>
                    <p>The schooner Adriana will be sold by the authorities here at public
                            auction in a few days.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>JAS. VIOSCA.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
